After a rough morning, I was wandering around my new neighborhood and stumbled upon this place. I must’ve went into every other restaurant in a 3-block radius but this place stole my heart. The people who work here make you feel right at home, they are so genuine and easygoing it makes eating here way better than any upscale restaurant. I’m from Hawaii, not NYC and this is one of the first places that’s felt like home since I got here. The food is also fantastic and a great value. I got a Lamb Gyro (which only lasted on my plate about 10 mins) and killer fries, super crispy outside with melt in your mouth potato goodness inside. One of the gentlemen behind the counter made me the BEST cinnamon cappuccino which I drank on my walk home. This place definitely has soul, and I will definitely be back. Thanks Tony’s for making my day a little better :)

I ordered food from here yesterday for the first time. It was fantastic n now one of my favs n goin up near the top of “the list” for sure! Anyone that’s seen my reviews knows that the details n specific requests n instructions r key. They got every detail perfect which doesn’t happen often enough. That’s not enough, of course. The food was fresh n delicious n I inhaled it as if I hadn’t eaten in days lol. In fact, I meant to take pics to upload but I got lost in my delicious meal so the only pic I have is the aftermath lmaoooooo. If ur in this part of Brooklyn u know food can be tough. Some good stuff but way overpriced...some reasonably priced stuff but not made with care n love n quality. Tony’s seems to me to be a great split of the two. I didn’t get robbed on the price n my meal was scrumptious n fresh n also correct to 100% accuracy. Let’s see if the next one is also perfect n fresh n delicious. I’d try them if ur in the area, I was impressed enough to write this encyclopedia of a review! The aftermath pic shows the wreckage. I inhaled every last bite!!!

They wouldn't offer to remake the pizza or even look into why it was made in a completely incorrect style. Both my uncle and I tried calling and couldn't reach a manager nor anyone with any knowledge of the business. The lady who answered the phone was rude and unwelcoming to both the local and out of state phone numbers. My uncle and I are highly disappointed with the poor service and messed up order.
